      "body": "One thing to keep in mind here, is the increased likelyhood of spurious CI failures when running on experimental distros. Packages can be changing daily, and can be mis-packaged, or broken in various ways, causing build failures or other issues. The same `apt install x y z` invocation won't necessarily work one day to the next etc. We've seen this somewhat with debian:experimental.",
