      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Thanks, I'm fully aware that we may see random failures. My thinking is that it's still worth it in the end. It's probably a good idea to run these tests as nightly tests and not for PRs, so that random failures don't get in the way of normal dev work. \r\n\r\n> We've seen this somewhat with debian:experimental.\r\n\r\nHas this been used in Core? I wasn't aware, and I'm happy to hear more about your experiences. \r\n\r\nI could imagine that apt.llvm.org is the better choice for clang, so we'd need debian:experimental only for gcc.\r\n",
